# Form Menu library (PEP Web)

The **Form Menu** preview page (`/preview/form-menu`, sidebar: **Block → Form Menu**) is the source of truth for multi-section form nav. Match [Figma Form_menu](https://www.figma.com/design/IZ6algHkFp6Z2a5dYiS1hC/PEP?node-id=477-19895).

## Page structure (`FormMenuBlockPage.tsx`)

| Section | Purpose | Registry |
|--------|---------|----------|
| **Notes** | Form_menu rules (states, active, required *) | Page copy |
| **Library** | Approved list-item variants | `FORM_MENU_STYLE_ROWS` where `tier: 'library'` |
| **Preview** | Composed form-nav example only — not a Library pick | Page-only demo |
| **Pending** | New styles under review | `tier: 'pending'` |

## Layout rules

1. Before coding a form section sidebar, check Library.
2. Compose with `FormMenu` + `FormMenuItem` from `@/components/form-menu`.
3. States: `complete` | `incomplete` | `nested`; set `active` on the current section.
4. If no Library match: add Pending row + preview, then use in layout.
5. Promote Pending → Library only when the user asks.

## Files

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `pep-web/src/components/form-menu.tsx` | `FormMenu`, `FormMenuItem` |
| `pep-web/src/data/form-menu-registry.ts` | Library / Pending tiers |
| `pep-web/src/pages/FormMenuBlockPage.tsx` | Block page UI |

## Anti-patterns

- Rebuilding Form_menu markup only inside a demo page without a registry entry.
- Using Dropdown Menu for this vertical form section nav.
